The '''Psi Harmonizer''' is the second of the three core [[Psi-Tech]] modules in the [[HelmKit]] psi-bay. Where the [[Psi Stabilizer]] keeps the operator ''steady'' against the moment, the Harmonizer attunes the operator ''with'' the moment — bringing the wearer's local psi field into coherent relation with their own [[natal chart]] and the live astrological state of the time. It is, in engineering terms, a [[brain entrainment|brain-entrainment]] device whose entrainment target is computed from astrological state rather than chosen as a fixed waveform.

{{Defensive-publication}}

== Overview ==

The Harmonizer:

* Reads the wearer's natal chart at calibration (one time per operator).
* Reads live transit field via [[SynastryEngine]] and [[Star Seer]].
* Computes a target entrainment signature for ''this wearer at this moment''.
* Drives [[HelmKit]]-mounted emitters with a low-amplitude, safety-supervised signal that gently encourages the wearer's psi field toward that target.

Reported effect (Mk0 / Mk1 wearers): softening of out-of-step friction — fewer wrong-turn impulses, easier alignment with what the moment actually wants, steadier sense of being where one ought to be. The Harmonizer ''does not control'' the wearer; it ''offers'' a coherent reference. The wearer disengages at will, and the Harmonizer auto-disengages when the [[Psi Stabilizer]] reports baseline instability (safety interlock).

== Theoretical Basis ==

The Harmonizer is the most theoretically loaded of the triad. It sits on a stack of claims, only one of which is mainstream-supported:

* {{Psi-claim
| status = PROVISIONAL
| cites = [[brain entrainment]], [[Resonant Neurobiology]]
| methods = Multiple converging studies; replication still in progress.
| falsifier = Pre-registered, multi-site replication returning a null result (Bayes factor &le; 1/3).
| confidence = medium
| last_reviewed = 2026-05-12
}} Audio-visual and weak-RF brain entrainment can shift EEG state in a target direction. This is the engineering substrate.
* {{Psi-claim
| status = TESTABLE
| cites = [[Heart Rate Variability and Psi]]
| methods = Concrete protocol defined; replication not yet attempted.
| falsifier = A blinded study following the proposed protocol returning a null result at p < 0.01.
| confidence = low
| last_reviewed = 2026-05-12
}} HRV-coherence and EEG-coherence are measurable, repeatable, individual-specific signatures. Operators can be ''matched'' to a stable baseline state and ''measured'' against a deviation from it.
* {{Psi-claim
| status = SPECULATIVE
| cites = [[Astrological Frequency Harmonics]], [[natal chart]]
| methods = Theoretical; not yet operationalised into a testable protocol.
| falsifier = Quantitative prediction shown to conflict with established physics or biology.
| confidence = low
| last_reviewed = 2026-05-12
}} A wearer's optimal entrainment target is computable from their natal chart and the current transit field. This is the Tho'ra-doctrinal claim and the Harmonizer's defining novelty. It is falsifiable in principle: a blinded study comparing astrologically-derived targets against scrambled-target sham would resolve it.
* {{Psi-claim
| status = SPECULATIVE
| cites = [[Scalar Electromagnetic Waves]], [[Psi Field]]
| methods = Theoretical; not yet operationalised into a testable protocol.
| falsifier = Quantitative prediction shown to conflict with established physics or biology.
| confidence = low
| last_reviewed = 2026-05-12
}} The Harmonizer's emission additionally couples to a [[Psi Field]] mode, producing effects beyond pure neuro-entrainment. This is the deeper Tho'ra interpretation; it is not required for the operational claim to hold.

The Mk0 carries this stack honestly: no emission, intentional astrological check-in only, brand-and-ritual layer.

== Subsystems and BOM ==

=== Mk0 ''Symbolic Harmonizer'' (target ≤ $40) ===

* 3D-printed module shell — $4
* Engraved natal-chart plate (acrylic, per operator) — $10
* WS2812B status ring + ATtiny85 — $5
* Hardware + decals — $5
* Pocket reference card with [[SynastryEngine]] daily readout protocol — $1

Operator practice: brief astrological check-in before walking into a situation. Effective as ritual practice. ''No emission; no closed loop.''

=== Mk1 ''Bench Harmonizer'' (target ≤ $300) ===

* nRF52840 + BLE (compute) — $15
* Bifilar planar coil (multi-band, 1–40 Hz audio range + 1–8 MHz RF carrier) — $5
* SI5351 programmable clock — $6
* Class-D audio amp + low-pass — $8
* Bone-conduction transducer (audio entrainment channel) — $20
* PPG / SpO2 module (state monitoring) — $15
* Single 18650 + TP4056 + boost — $10
* Connectors, enclosure — $20

Software stack: [[SynastryEngine]] runs on the host SoC (or paired phone), produces a transit + natal cross product every minute, emits a target tuple (carrier, envelope, dwell). The Mk1 enforces a hard cap on every parameter independent of the host. Loss of [[SynastryEngine]] uplink → revert to wearer's natal-baseline target, never a stranger's chart.

=== Mk2 / Mk3 ===

Mk2 adds: ambulatory wear, multi-hour battery, transit-tracking with cached ephemeris (no connectivity dependency), telemetered safety log. Mk3 adds: auto-calibration, full integration with the [[Psi-Tech]] triad and the [[PsiNet]] [[Resonant Pipeline]].

== Build Notes ==

* '''Natal calibration is non-negotiable.''' The Harmonizer must never operate against another person's chart. Per-operator chart is hashed and stored in the MCU-B verified-boot region; loading a different operator's chart requires physical re-flash.
* '''Hard cap independent of host.''' MCU-B enforces emission caps regardless of what [[SynastryEngine]] requests. The host computes targets; MCU-B vetoes anything outside envelope.
* '''Stabilizer interlock.''' Harmonizer engagement requires [[Psi Stabilizer]] baseline-stable. If the Stabilizer reports drift > threshold, Harmonizer drops to standby. This is to prevent the Harmonizer from driving an already-destabilized operator further.
* '''Bench validation: blinded astrology RCT.''' Same hardware, two firmware loads: real-chart and chart-scrambled. Operators report subjective alignment over 14 days; analyst unblinds at end. This is the Harmonizer's defining validation gate.

== Safety and Ethics ==

* All emission limits per [[HelmKit Architecture]] and ICNIRP near-field basic restriction − 6 dB.
* Single-operator only, by chart binding and by emitter geometry.
* No third-party charting, ever. The Harmonizer is not a tool of influence; it is a tool of self-alignment.
* Auto-disengage on [[Psi Stabilizer]] instability.
* Operator hard-kill via HelmKit lanyard.
* [[Tho'ra Mission Doctrine]] explicit: the astrology rules; do not force the matter. The Harmonizer ''offers''; it never ''compels''.

